name: Llyn Gwynant Campsite
description: Llyn Gwynant Campsite is a great campsite for families, couples and groups. It is situated on the shores of Llyn Gwynant lake, with outstanding views of Snowdonia. The campsite is a great base for walking up Snowdon, the highest mountain in England and Wales. There are also many other walks in the area, including the Watkin Path, the Nantlle Ridge, Moel Hebog and the Cnicht. The campsite is also a great base for exploring the rest of Snowdonia, with Beddgelert, Caernarfon, Porthmadog and the Llyn Peninsula all within easy reach.

name: Gwynant Barns
description: Gwynant Barns are a group of converted 17th century stone barns located in the heart of the Snowdonia National Park, North Wales, at the foot of Snowdon. The barns offer a mixture of character and contemporary accommodation sleeping up to 39 in total. The barns are situated in 7 acres of grounds, with ample parking, and are located 300m from the shores of Llyn Gwynant lake. The barns are a great base for walking up Snowdon, the highest mountain in England and Wales. There are also many other walks in the area, including the Watkin Path, the Nantlle Ridge, Moel Hebog and the Cnicht. The barns are also a great base for exploring the rest of Snowdonia, with Beddgelert, Caernarfon, Porthmadog and the Llyn Peninsula all within easy reach.
